(1, 532, 'Danielle Poirier', '+1(435)671-0504', '2018-02-04', '22:42:00', 'dp.danielle.dp@gmail.com', 'I am inquiring about seasonal employment opportunities for the upcoming winter season. I would like to learn about any positions you may be hiring: guiding, ski lessons, customer service, marketing web design management, cooking, cleaning, retail, reservations, etc. \n\nI currently work at Patagonia and help manage the @patagoniaslc Instagram and just completed an internship with Ski Utah, a marketing organization. I helped manage the @skiutah Instagram account as well as helped with content creation and blogs for skiutah.com and I have also worked for a local nonprofit, Wasatch Backcountry Alliance as the content and outreach coordinator. I worked in the Environmental & Sustainability Studies office at the University of Utah. Tasks included event planning, fundraising, outreach & communication, budget processing, marketing, and newsletter and video production. I wrote blog articles for the Sustainability Office at the University as well. I ran the website and newsletters for Water From the Moon, a travel boutique in my home town. I have worked for City Weekly, a local news organization, on their marketing team. I have a lot of experience I can contribute to your team. \n\n\nI have skied since I could walk and have lived in Colorado, Canada, and Utah. I grew up with a dad who coached for the US and Canadian Nordic Olympic teams, so ski culture is very much a part of me. I am an avid backcountry skier, as well as resort and cross country skiing. I have also worked numerous customer service and office organizational jobs. I am a self-sufficient, hard -working, excited and easy going individual and would be a great fit on your team! \n\nI speak Spanish, but not yet fluent. Please see my attached resume and let me know if there are any positions applicable or where I can find employment information. \n\nCheers, \nDani Poirier \nwww.linkedin.com/in/daniellepoirierutah/\ndp.danielle.dp@gmail.com\n+1(435)671-0504', 3),
